medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Patient presents with 36 hours of abdominal pain. The pain initially woke her from sleep and was in the epigastric region. The pain then migrated to the right lower quadrant (RLQ) and worsened with movement and car rides. The patient also experienced nausea but no vomiting. There has been a decrease in oral intake due to nausea. She denies any fever, chills, or anorexia.
